196
00:11:06,680 --> 00:11:09,520
Cologne doesn't suit me, anyhow...

197
00:11:09,990 --> 00:11:12,040
Why are you acting so coy?

198
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:19,110
Cologne, huh? 
I hated that about him, too.

199
00:11:19,910 --> 00:11:24,200
He left home 
soon after Al was born.

200
00:11:24,890 --> 00:11:29,460
Mom always said he was off studying alchemy,

201
00:11:29,460 --> 00:11:32,080
but he never once 
even sent us a letter.

202
00:11:32,080 --> 00:11:38,070
And yet, the scent of that cologne he wore 
always permeated the house.

203
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,510
Earlier, when I saw Lyra in Liore,

204
00:11:40,510 --> 00:11:43,000
